> Hi,
>
> Assuming your distributor is constructed the same as those for VW flat 4s
I have dealt with...
>
> At the bottom of the distributor there is a ring with teeth offset to one
side that mesh with the gear inside of the crank case. They should be offset
in the same direction as the rotor arm points.
> The ring is held on by a split pin that goes right through the shaft - so
if the pin were removed the ring could be rotated 180 degrees and the pin
replaced. thus rotating the distributor 180 degrees.
> You would have two self canceling errors and the vacuum canister could be
aligned to a position were it does not foul anything.
>
> I must emphasize that I have not done this,  so do not know of any
problems with the setup; any insights from others welcome.
>
> Good luck
> Bob Wallace
> Bristol UK
> 1998 T2
I have just been informed that the 050 is not vacuum advance ( I have not
seen it yet) So that problem is solved..
